	abstract = {In this ﬁrst paper, the confocal technique for ﬁbre-orientation distribution measurement is described and the associated errors discussed in detail. With this technique, ﬁbres are followed for short distances into the bulk of the sample enabling a complete description of the ﬁbre-orientation distribution tensor. Novel image processing and management routines have been implemented in order fully to automate the data acquisition, and consequently signiﬁcant sample areas (several square mm) can be analysed within hours. In a follow-up paper the ﬁbre-orientation measurements from the confocal technique will be used to evaluate independently the errors in the standard 2D image analysis technique of ﬁbre-orientation measurement. \# 2001 Published by Elsevier Science Ltd. All rights reserved.},
